 . but hey! That's no fun! :-p<br><br>In these forums I want you to post things basically about your guild, maybe what we'd find on your website or otherwise without having to leave this forum to find it. For example, some ideas for things that you can post about your guild are:<br><br>1. Guild Leader - Name, alts, email address, play times, IRL first names (Hey we're all friends here right?)<br>2. Roster - I know these will get out of date and you may not even keep one, but a quick roster could help so when people see such and such a name in the channel they can go &quot;Hey! I know that person s/he's from Velious Knights!&quot;<br>3. Raid Leader or Raid Rules - Some guilds have specific raid leaders who you can contact if you want to set things up. . or some guilds just have peoplew ho like to lead raids more than others and once this information is posted it would allow people to get in touch with them in need be. Also some guilds may have specific raid rules, or even a link to rules which we may browse in case we'd like to get more information.<br>4. Level range of the people in your guild - Sometimes people forget that not everyone enjoys or is yet in the higher end game. We must not forget these people! If you are a smaller guild that maybe has people in the lower level range, let us know about it so others in the same situation can be reached and you can get to know them.<br>5. Individuals, introduce yourselves! If you're in the guild then please say that you're in it! Tell us how long you've been a member, what you love about your guild and what you most enjoy doing with your guild! You could also share one fond memory about something you've done with your guild. . hey we're all friends here why not tell us a story? How about letting us know your play times or favorite places to hunt?<br>6. General guild goals and accomplishments - Has your guild always wanted to lead a succesful plane raid? Tell us! Did such and such a player just hit X level that they were really trying for, and you're really proud of them? Let us know! This can be a place for general announcements as well as any news you'd like to share.<br>7. Anything else! The world is your oyster. Dive in and grab that pearl. Share anything you feel like sharing so we can get to know you!<br><br>This forum is just a trial, for now. . but if it catches on we can add to it and make it a permanent part of our message boards. For now, please introduce yourselves and we'll move from there. Only when we communicate can we move on.<br><br>&quot;The moment we stop believing that democracy can work, is the day that we lose it.&quot; - That one girl from Star Wars. . I think.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E4E9EF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub66.ezboard.com/usanida.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sanida</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Honored Guest</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#B76D00>(8/5/02 5:17:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub66.ezboard.com/fthelanyscoalitionofguildsfrm48.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Arma Aquetatis - The ball is in your court!</span><hr size=1> Well here is basically what I posted in the council section, will edit with other info soon<br><br>Leader - High council<br><br>High Council - Lrrac, Pynne, Gandil, Sanida, Locathia, Carllie<br><br>LCG Reps - Sanida, Gymli (raid officer)<br><br>Members - 25 approx<br>link to Arma's current list of members <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub9.ezboard.com/farmaaquetatisthearmaranks.showMessage?topicID=414.topic">pub9.ezboard.com/farmaaquetatisthearmaranks.showMessage?topicID=414.topic</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br><br>Average level - 46+ heavy with mains, 20-35 heavy with alts<br><br>Class Wise - on the 45+ range we are tank heavy with a few cleric/druids, 35 to 45 is 